SIMPLE: unlikely
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlikely
<hw>Un*like"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not likely;
improbable; not to be reasonably expected; <as>as, an <ex>unlikely</ex>
event; the thing you mention is very <ex>unlikely</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not holding out a prospect of success; likely to
fail; unpromising; <as>as, <ex>unlikely</ex> means</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not such as to inspire liking; unattractive;
disagreeable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>unlikely</xex>
eld of me.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlikely</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unlikely
<hw>Un*like"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an unlikely
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unliken</ent>⟦br⟧
